cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper proposes a new technique for enhancing computer vision tasks by introducing a content-based spatial adaptation mechanism. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a new unit that can be used in deep neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a differentiable kernel selection mechanism, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of deep neural networks and experimentation with different image processing tasks could also place the paper in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
